: 4080.48317}, {"time": "2026-07-22 10:00:00", "open": 4079.96427, "high": 4100.88169, "low": 4076.64085, "close": 4096.42423}, {"time": "2026-07-22 11:00:00", "open": 4095.64207, "high": 4123.75596, "low": 4095.64207, "close": 4121.80557}, {"time": "2026-07-22 12:00:00", "open": 4121.42109, "high": 4130.35397, "low": 4119.63418, "close": 4129.10479}, {"time": "2026-07-22 13:00:00", "open": 4128.41645, "high": 4140.78675, "low": 4128.41645, "close": 4131.36101}], "calendar": [], "editorial": "Gold finds itself at a genuinely interesting crossroads this Wednesday morning, with spot XAU/USD trading around 4,131 after a clean recovery rally off the lows printed earlier in the week. The daily chart tells a story of a market that has been through considerable turbulence over the past month, and the current picture is one of tentative stabilisation rather than clear directional conviction \u2014 hence the neutral bias carried into today's session.\n\nZooming out across the last thirty daily candles, the structure story is one of a sharp peak, a brutal retracement, and now a recovery attempt that has yet to prove itself. Gold carved out a high above 4,200 in early July before sellers took control decisively, dragging price down through the 4,000 psychological level on multiple occasions. The prior reaction zone sitting around 3,957 has been tested three times and has, so far, held its ground as meaningful structure support. That level represents the line in the sand for the broader recovery thesis \u2014 a sustained break beneath it would materially alter the medium-term read. To the upside, the 4,206 area has registered four prior reactions and now sits as the nearest meaningful resistance overhead. Price has not been able to close above that zone since the early July peak, and it remains the first significant structural hurdle for any sustained bullish continuation.\n\nThe intraday picture on the H1 chart is more encouraging for the bulls in the near term. From yesterday afternoon's lows around the 4,043 area, price has staged a clean, progressive grind higher through the Asian and early European sessions, with each hourly candle building on the last. The move through 4,100 during the London morning was particularly notable \u2014 that level had capped price on several recent intraday attempts. The current 4,131 print represents the highest close seen since the 13th July, and momentum on the shorter timeframe is clearly pointing upward. The question the desk is watching is whether this intraday impulse has the structural follow-through to challenge the 4,206 prior reaction zone, or whether it fades into that supply area as it has done previously.\n\nWith no calendar events scheduled for today, the session is likely to be driven purely by technical flow and positioning dynamics. The absence of macro catalysts cuts both ways \u2014 there is no obvious trigger to accelerate a breakout, but equally nothing to derail the current intraday momentum abruptly. Liquidity conditions may thin during the North American afternoon, which can occasionally amplify moves in either direction.\n\nThe read would turn more constructive on a daily close above 4,206 with conviction. Conversely, a failure to hold the 4,075 to 4,080 area on any intraday pullback \u2014 a zone that provided support through the early European session \u2014 would suggest the recovery is struggling to build a credible base, and attention would return to the 3,957 structure support below.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}